reviews_data.review_text: Love this place! Rosie is the best, I honestly show up 99% of the time because of her! Recommend this place to everyone and esp love the way Rosie runs the show!!!

Food took forever, carne Asada tacos were terrible meat not steak, took an hour to get them. Served cold french fries after 30 minutes. Manager wipped glasses with his shirt. Bar had to be ripped before we could sit. I could go on. Never going back..don't go
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We’re so sorry that your visit to Rally didn’t reflect the quality experience that we pride ourselves on. You deserved a better experience.

We'd love to connect directly to see how we can make this right, and we’re already working with our team to ensure no guest has to go through that again. We know this may feel like too little, too late, and we truly regret that what should have been a great visit was ruined. 

Thank you for sharing your open and honest feedback. We’re learning from it, and we hope that at some point in the future we are able to welcome you back into Rally and give you the experience you deserve. Please let us know if this is possible.

reviews_data.review_text:
This place is hit or miss the pickle ball side the food was no good the service was bad, they forget about who they service the food was never hot had to send it back to get re cooked the chicken wings were raw in the middle not cooked correctly.

The games are great plenty of time to play that was a great plus , the restrooms are amazingly cleaned .

Their restaurant side the food was great, the service was also great, is owned by the same people don't understand why one side is better then the other , it is what it is though.

We had a good time and is all that matters to us.

We're very disappointed that we've been inconsistent with your experiences at Rally. We value your feedback and ensure you that we will use it to get better. 

We hope that you'll give us another opportunity to deliver the experience that you deserve.

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic atmosphere, wonderful staff - great for dropping in for coffee or lunch, working remote, playing pickleball, and for hosting events.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Appreciate the support! We can’t wait to see you back soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Morgan is absolutely a gem!! A long days work to seeing a smiling/ lively Energy was amazing! Thank you guys, can’t wait to be back to see her!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for sharing your experience. We love to hear our employees taking care of our guests.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the nicest, best maintained pickleball facility I e played at. The check in process is quick and then you are escorted to your private lounge area attached to your court. The staff checks in regularly to be sure everything is okay, which is a nice touch.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words! We’re thrilled Rally delivered for you, and we hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
My first experience at Rally was as a volunteer for the Coffee Club which is a non-profit that helps feed the unhoused of Charlotte. Rally gave a space to this organization to create snack bags and make sandwiches for the unhoused. This was the beginning of my curiosity of the game of pickleball and this place called, Rally.

Several months later, I signed up for a Rookies course to learn the game of pickleball. The instructor, Rosie, was immediately welcoming when I showed up. As an introvert, I needed this warm welcome to feel comfortable. The course was fantastic and after an hour of learning how to "dink" and find out what a "kitchen"  was I was hooked and an hour became too short.

With each weekly class, I made friends, learned more pickleball lingo, upskilled, and felt so comfortable playing pickleball I found myself staying afterwards to watch others play and signed up for socials, shuffles, courts and coffee and other events. The staff was welcoming, remembered my name and encouraged this learning journey.

Stack all of that with a delicious menu, from a delicious wood-fire pizza, caesar salad with chicken skewers, protein shakes, burgers, tacos...I've nearly tried it all...this place has all the stars from me. OH and wonderful cocktails.

It's for all these reasons (and many more) Rally has easily become my "third place" - my Central Perk, Cheers, MacLaren's, Paddy's Pub...and I would highly recommend you check out this place. Whether you are looking for a pickleball spot that's a little more social then other spots; a good bite to eat; some great people watching over a drink or a nice breakfast spot to catch up with a friend or have your next "out of office" work chat...I would check out Rally.

reviews_data.owner_answer: We can’t thank you enough for the five stars! Hearing that you continue to have an amazing time at Rally is exactly why we do what we do. From the courts to the café to the social vibe, our goal is always to create a place where people can play, connect, and have fun. We look forward to your next visit.

reviews_data.review_text: Such an accepting environment! Any level experience welcomed. I had the fall coffee flight which was so good! The staff is very helpful and friendly. Plenty of functional and eye appealing sitting areas
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for stopping by! We'll be sure to share the flight feedback with our café team.

reviews_data.review_text: This is the COOLEST place I have been to. From the food to the pickeball, everything was fantastic. The staff was so friendly and made you feel welcome. Rosie was awesome and very attentive every step of the way.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We agree: Rosie is awesome! We're happy to hear you had an outstanding experience with us, and we look forward to seeing you on the courts again soon.
